  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Assets Building for Livelihoods and Environmental Sustainability for South-East Luzon (CABLES- South Luzon)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Bicol region is often exposed to natural perils like typhoons, volcanic eruptions and earthquakes.  In 2004 and lately in 2006, a series of typhoons hit the Bicol region  which triggered flooding, landslides and strong winds that caused heavy damages to agriculture land and residential areas.  There was also mudflow from the slopes of Mayon Volcano in Albay province that ravaged several villages and farms.   

This project will help restore the livelihood of many affected families in these areas through livestock-based farming interventions, natural resource management and disaster preparedness. A total of 1452 families (499 original and 953 pass-ons) will form into self-help groups.  Original families will receive 178 water buffalo, 187 cattle, 952 goats, 62 pigs, 44 bee colony  along with seeds, seedlings, tools, and micro-credit funds for initiating income generating activities.  Training on Heifer&#x2019;s Cornerstones and PSRP, animal husbandry, sustainable agriculture skills, natural resource management and other topics will be provided.  The project will also support a community-based disaster preparedness program and natural resources management to enhance community resilience to natural disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
